    "comment": "Rationale: The authors have used peroxidase staining (Fig. 1 G-I) and immunogold-labelling (Fig. 1 J-L) in the CA1 stratum radiatum to localize L1 immunoreactivity at presynaptic sites of asymmetric synapses.\nOn immunoblots, the antibody shows two bands of 200 kDa and 80 kDa (Fig. 4). The antibody was originally described in PMID:12697052.\n\n12/02/2021 Dnyanada: The term \"integral component...\" was chosen based on the association of L1 immunogold particles with the presynaptic membrane as well as on its transmembrane topology (as described in UniProt: L1CAM_MOUSE).\n\nThe paper uses Western blot to characterize the anti-L1 antibody, the ~200kD band is indicative of L1CAM and the ~80kD band can be attributed to enzymatic cleavage. Similar immunoblot results are seen in PMID:12697052 for mouse neuropil and cells transfected with L1CAM. The mock-transfected cells do not show the ~200kD and ~80kD band indicating specificity.. Experimental description: \"Production of NP-/- mice was described by Hirata et al. (Hirata et al., 2001).\" p.1348",
